Lib leader Nick Clegg is trailing Labour by 2 per cent in Sheffield Hallam . 
  Mr Clegg won his seat in 2010 by a huge margin . 
  He is to embark on three days of door knocking in his formally rock-solid constituency . 
  Tory peer Lord Ashcroft says 36 per cent of voters are now planning to vote for Labour . 
  Lib Dem leader insists he is 'confident but not complacent' in his seat . 
  He won the seat by a wide margin in 2010 with more than 50 per cent . 
 